      "description": "Cattle egrets — stocky white herons that have achieved one of the most remarkable natural range expansions in ornithological history. Originally confined to Africa and southern Asia, cattle egrets colonised South America by the early 20th century, spread through the Americas to North America by the 1950s, and have since established themselves on every inhabited continent. They follow large grazing animals — or tractors and lawn mowers — to catch invertebrates flushed by their movements.",
